  "report": {
    "narrative": [
      "In the 2026-03-01..2026-03-24 historical window, the hottest GPUs surfaced by the available ROCm telemetry are concentrated on the k002-004-v* host family, all reported on GPU card 0, with peak temperatures in the low 80s °C. A secondary cluster of elevated temperatures appears on k002-003 across multiple cards (2/4/6) but at lower levels (high 60s/low 70s °C).\n\nTop thermal outliers (highest priority):\n- k002-004-v5:8000 card0 @ 82°C\n- k002-004-v7:8000 card0 @ 81°C\n- k002-004-v1:8000 card0 @ 79°C\nNext tier:\n- k002-004-v8:8000 card0 @ 76°C\n- k002-004-v6:8000 card0 @ 75°C\nComparator / lower urgency:\n- k002-003:8000 card4 @ 72°C; card2 @ 71°C; card6 @ 69°C\n\nHost-context pattern: multiple distinct k002-004-v* nodes appear in the top list, and all are card0. That pattern is consistent with at least three plausible explanations: (1) workload placement repeatedly loading GPU0 more heavily than other GPUs, (2) a systematic cooling/airflow/fan-curve issue affecting that host family/rack segment, or (3) partial instrumentation (only GPU0 being exported on those nodes). The preview does not include per-card utilization, VRAM pressure, power, fan RPM, inlet temps, or throttling flags, so we cannot distinguish “hot due to high activity” from “hot due to cooling deficiency.”\n\nCorrelation to GPU activity / workload (limits): this panel’s preview contains temperature only. The adjacent scheduler panels show backlog concentration in partitions mi3001x (36 pending) and mi2104x (26 pending), but there is no node<->partition mapping or job-to-node attribution in the preview, so we cannot link k002-004-v* hotspots to a specific partition or user/job with high confidence.\n\nInvestigation order (practical triage):\n1) k002-004-v5 card0 and k002-004-v7 card0: confirm whether these were sustained peaks and check for throttling.\n2) k002-004-v1 card0: compare against other GPUs on the same node (not shown here) to detect a single-GPU cooling anomaly.\n3) k002-004-v8/v6 card0: monitor as they are part of the same cluster of hot nodes.\n4) k002-003 cards: lower priority unless users report performance/instability.\n\nConfidence: high that the listed accelerators are the hottest in the provided preview sample; low-to-moderate on “most stressed” overall because activity, power, VRAM, and fault signals are absent in the preview extract."
    ],
